#: ../../docs/training_manual/create_vector_data/forms.rst:2
msgid "Lesson: Forms"
msgstr "Pamoka: formos"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/create_vector_data/forms.rst:4
msgid ""
"When you add new data via digitizing, you're presented with a dialog that "
"lets you fill in the attributes for that feature. However, this dialog is "
"not, by default, very nice to look at. This can cause a usability problem, "
"especially if you have large datasets to create, or if you want other people"
" to help you digitize and they find the default forms to be confusing."
msgstr ""
"Kai jūs pridedate naujus duomenis skaitmenizuodami, jums pateikiamas "
"dialogas, kuriame jūs užpildote geoobjekto atributus. Bet pagal nutylėjimas "
"šis dialogas nėra labai malonus akiai. Tai gali sukelti patogumo problemų, "
"ypač jei jums reikia sukurti didelius duomenų rinkinius, arba jei jūs "
"norite, kad kiti žmonės padėtų skaitmeninti ir jiems numatytosios formos "
"atrodo painios."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/create_vector_data/forms.rst:11
msgid ""
"Fortunately, QGIS lets you create your own custom dialogs for a layer. This "
"lesson shows you how."
msgstr ""
"Laimei QGIS leidžia jums kurti jūsų savus sluoksnių dialogus. Ši pamoka "
"parodys kaip."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/create_vector_data/forms.rst:15
msgid "**The goal for this lesson:** To create a form for a layer."
msgstr "**Šios pamokos tikslas:** sukurti sluoksnio formą."

